  m_text: "\tIn Ancient Greece, Orpheus and Eurydice were happily married, until
    one day Eurydice was tragically bitten by a snake, and died.\n\tArmed with his
    lyre, Orpheus traveled to the Underworld, and met Hades. Hades agreed to let
    Orpheus bring Eurydice back with him, under the condition that until exiting
    the Underworld, Orpheus was not allowed to turn around to look at Eurydice behind
    him.\n\tNow, the pair travel through the Underworld to return home..."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
